  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Nutrition With Amaranth</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children 0 to 18</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project helps improve the nutritional status of infants, children and young people from 5 communities in the municipality of San Pablo Anicano, Puebla, by

&#x2022;	Measuring and monitoring the nutritional status of the children affiliated with our local partner. 

&#x2022;	Building capacity through nutritional counseling and training in culinary techniques for mothers of beneficiary children.

&#x2022;	Household production of organic amaranth cereal by building home gardens, giving priority to families of children with detected high levels of malnutrition and / or anemia.

&#x2022;	At the end of a year the nutritional status of children presenting anemia and malnutrition will be solved or improved by 80%.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Detection of anemia and/or malnutrition on children aged 0 to 18, by biometric and anthropometric studies. 
&#x2022;	Nutritional counseling through workshops for mothers and children.
&#x2022;	Training for families and conditioning of 100 home gardens for amaranth seed production.</narrative>
  </description>
